Target Group is nothing but a group of ec2-instances

For example we have 2 servers related to App servers and having more servers related to for sonarqube having 1 server, to maintain eks have 1 server like this having different different
servers, Traffic should need to be distribute in these 2 App servers only for that 2 App servers we need to make a Group for it called as Target Group

Go to AWS Dashboard ---------> select Target Group ---------> Create Target Group ----------> Target Group Name: MyTargetGroup -------> Port: 80 --------> next

select 2 servers----------> include as pending below --------> next -----------> create target group 

